### Auth API Testing with REST Client Extension

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@username = testuser
@email = test@example.com
@password = password123

### 1. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### 2. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Login user
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 4. Get current user info (requires token from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### 5. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### 6. Test with invalid credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "wronguser",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### 7. Test accessing protected endpoint without token
GET {{baseUrl}}/me
